00:30:50,040 --> 00:30:53,500
you took away that happiness from me.

250
00:30:54,580 --> 00:30:56,970
I resented you...

251
00:30:58,110 --> 00:31:00,690
the entire time I was in there.

252
00:31:20,940 --> 00:31:23,650
After the old woman and the child died,

253
00:31:24,450 --> 00:31:26,770
were you at peace?

254
00:31:30,850 --> 00:31:32,920
I'm sure you weren't.

255
00:31:35,580 --> 00:31:38,180
There's nothing in this world...

256
00:31:40,240 --> 00:31:45,010
that can console your heart right now.

257
00:31:54,040 --> 00:31:56,960
Just let me do what I can.

258
00:31:57,930 --> 00:32:02,240
Don't complicate things any more.

259
00:32:31,540 --> 00:32:35,660
<i>Cheongwu House</i>

260
00:32:53,790 --> 00:32:56,160
- Did you make a reservation?
- Yes.

261
00:33:07,370 --> 00:33:10,480
Why are you here?

262
00:33:13,850 --> 00:33:15,930
Hello.

263
00:33:16,630 --> 00:33:20,060
Assemblyman Jeong is on his way.

264
00:33:20,060 --> 00:33:24,700
There's something I must tell you before that.

265
00:33:33,620 --> 00:33:36,210
My boys are dead.

266
00:33:36,210 --> 00:33:40,540
Lee Sang Taek, Lee Sang Taek's mother and daughter,

267
00:33:40,540 --> 00:33:45,240
Jeong Hae Yong, a few underlings, and Jo Bin.

268
00:33:45,240 --> 00:33:47,260
Do you know what else?

269
00:33:47,260 --> 00:33:52,940
I have to live in fear of Chairman Kim Kang Heon coming after me every day.

270
00:33:52,940 --> 00:33:57,080
Why do I have to live like that?

271
00:33:57,080 --> 00:34:00,250
Whose fault is this?

272
00:34:00,250 --> 00:34:03,640
If you turn a blind eye on us, Judge Song,

273
00:34:03,640 --> 00:34:08,990
we also can't help but hold a grudge against you.

274
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:15,080
What do you need me to do?

275
00:34:16,870 --> 00:34:21,240
I don't know what your plan is,

276
00:34:21,240 --> 00:34:25,450
but you have to guarantee our survival in the future.

277
00:34:33,850 --> 00:34:36,000
Damn it.

278
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:38,890
Judge Song is here. Why aren't you here yet?

279
00:34:38,890 --> 00:34:42,950
Oh, I'm so sorry! The event ended so late.

280
00:34:42,950 --> 00:34:46,130
Yes, you two have a talk.

281
00:34:46,130 --> 00:34:49,710
Yes. I'm almost there.

282
00:34:49,710 --> 00:34:51,440
Okay.

283
00:34:54,690 --> 00:34:56,930
He said he'll be here soon.

284
00:35:20,950 --> 00:35:22,910
Man!

285
00:35:27,130 --> 00:35:31,210
Fifty years of hard work was almost destroyed!

286
00:35:33,220 --> 00:35:34,790
Geez!

287
00:35:39,450 --> 00:35:41,060
<i>Judge Song,</i>

288
00:35:41,060 --> 00:35:43,960
please tell me your plan, too.

289
00:35:43,960 --> 00:35:46,640
I must know as well.

290
00:35:48,350 --> 00:35:54,040
Since last year, Assemblyman Jeong Yi Hwa has been making a recommendation to me.

291
00:35:54,040 --> 00:36:00,430
There was an order from the regime formed two years ago saying they needed me.

292
00:36:02,240 --> 00:36:04,900
I plan to enter the Blue House.

293
00:36:04,900 --> 00:36:06,610
With the Blue House's support,

294
00:36:06,610 --> 00:36:11,110
I'll be freed from Chairman Kim Gang Heon's threats.

295
00:36:18,140 --> 00:36:21,420
Is there anything we can do to help?

296
00:36:21,420 --> 00:36:25,690
Jeong Yi Hwa and I will take care of getting me in there.

297
00:36:25,690 --> 00:36:30,330
However, there's one thing that concerns me.

298
00:36:30,330 --> 00:36:34,770
Is the child named Lee Cheong Gang alive?

299
00:36:35,580 --> 00:36:37,620
Should I find out?

300
00:36:37,620 --> 00:36:41,000
Before Chairman Kim Kang Heon finds him,

301
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:44,340
please find him first and protect him.

302
00:36:44,340 --> 00:36:45,940
What's the reason?

303
00:36:45,940 --> 00:36:52,380
All of his family members were killed because of me.

304
00:36:52,380 --> 00:36:58,360
You want to protect your human conscience at this point?

305
00:37:03,640 --> 00:37:07,840
First off, your life and mine...

306
00:37:07,840 --> 00:37:12,250
Protect the lives that can be killed right now.

307
00:37:17,930 --> 00:37:19,670
Ta-da.

308
00:37:22,200 --> 00:37:24,290
Gosh, it's so funny.

309
00:37:24,290 --> 00:37:27,880
- What are you doing?
- It's a joke. Just kidding.

310
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:30,270
If there weren't a tail on you, Pan Ho,

311
00:37:30,270 --> 00:37:33,370
who would know the three of us are meeting here?

312
00:37:40,790 --> 00:37:43,070
<i>Eat before you go.</i>

313
00:37:43,890 --> 00:37:46,600
The really important talk begins now.

314
00:37:46,600 --> 00:37:49,270
Let's eat first. Take a seat.

315
00:37:55,030 --> 00:37:58,310
- Let's eat.
- Talk about what?

316
00:38:01,640 --> 00:38:04,710
Do you know who I met before coming here?

317
00:38:04,710 --> 00:38:07,030
That's why I came late.

318
00:38:08,620 --> 00:38:11,760
The VIP's (President's) Chief Secretary.

319
00:38:12,350 --> 00:38:16,530
We stalled for more than a year, you know.

320
00:38:16,530 --> 00:38:19,720
Do you know how anxious I was,

321
00:38:19,720 --> 00:38:23,050
thinking they might've changed their minds?

322
00:38:23,050 --> 00:38:24,580
I told him about you,

323
00:38:24,580 --> 00:38:27,330
and he put a cigarette in his mouth with a grin.

324
00:38:27,330 --> 00:38:29,400
He looked relieved.

325
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:32,860
At the same time, he said the current regime's motto

326
00:38:32,860 --> 00:38:37,660
from the elections two years ago was "novelty."

327
00:38:38,190 --> 00:38:41,020
It's called novelty if you put it nicely. You can also say

328
00:38:41,020 --> 00:38:43,800
it means they lack the background. Right?

329
00:38:44,570 --> 00:38:50,410
But the one additional topping they want to add on

330
00:38:50,410 --> 00:38:52,780
is respect.

331
00:38:53,680 --> 00:38:57,340
If you become the Chief of Political Affairs,

332
00:38:57,340 --> 00:39:02,520
this regime will gain dignity because you're flawless from any angle.

333
00:39:04,580 --> 00:39:08,700
Damn, this was Judge Song's only mistake!

334
00:39:08,700 --> 00:39:10,660
Sure.

335
00:39:10,660 --> 00:39:13,010
Let's say he's right.

336
00:39:13,010 --> 00:39:14,780
What?

337
00:39:17,140 --> 00:39:20,340
He said they'll let us know the time and location.

338
00:39:20,340 --> 00:39:22,540
So, let's meet them first and see.

339
00:39:23,140 --> 00:39:29,280
What kind of influence will Kim Sang Hyeok's trial have?

340
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:31,260
He's guilty.

341
00:39:33,940 --> 00:39:36,920
The exemplary judge who destroyed Woo One.

342
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:39,910
The last icon of justice left in our age

343
00:39:39,910 --> 00:39:42,480
who fights against an enormous corrupt force.

344
00:39:43,250 --> 00:39:46,150
If you become the Chief of Political Affairs,

345
00:39:46,150 --> 00:39:49,890
even Kim Kang Heon can't have his way with you.

346
00:39:53,640 --> 00:39:56,270
Assemblyman Jeong is at a restaurant called

347
00:39:56,270 --> 00:39:58,570
Cheongwu House on the outskirts of Woowon City.

348
00:39:58,570 --> 00:40:00,220
Three people are in the room.

349
00:40:00,220 --> 00:40:04,490
Judging by her car parked nearby, one of them is Jo Mi Yeon.

350
00:40:04,490 --> 00:40:07,010
But I can't tell who the other person is.

351
00:40:07,010 --> 00:40:10,450
I just texted you a photo of their shoes.

352
00:40:13,810 --> 00:40:15,830
<i>Woo One, Yu Tae Geun</i>

353
00:40:15,830 --> 00:40:18,670
Identify Judge Song Pan Ho's current location.

354
00:40:18,670 --> 00:40:20,750
<i>All right.</i>

355
00:40:34,930 --> 00:40:38,730
He's not at the gym. I'll search the nearby area.

356
00:40:39,900 --> 00:40:42,590
There's no time to think about it.

357
00:40:42,590 --> 00:40:46,540
If Chairman Kim finds out about this, all three of us

358
00:40:46,540 --> 00:40:48,800
will die without a trace.

359
00:40:48,800 --> 00:40:50,830
Once I get word from them,

360
00:40:50,830 --> 00:40:53,110
I'll arrange a meeting for that time.

361
00:40:53,110 --> 00:40:56,140
You just do as I say. Deal?

362
00:40:56,140 --> 00:40:57,860
Let's eat.

363
00:40:58,660 --> 00:41:00,790
I'll get going first.

364
00:41:00,790 --> 00:41:02,970
You should eat!

365
00:41:06,520 --> 00:41:08,990
Is that someone you know?

366
00:41:50,830 --> 00:41:53,430
Who was here with you?

367
00:41:54,780 --> 00:41:57,680
There were three of you. Where did one go?

368
00:41:57,680 --> 00:42:00,540
Is he talking about Wu Cheol?

369
00:42:03,130 --> 00:42:06,110
What are you doing here, Assemblyman?

370
00:42:06,110 --> 00:42:08,250
Who are you?

371
00:42:54,320 --> 00:42:57,240
- Search every corner.
- Yes, sir!

372
00:45:06,550 --> 00:45:08,920
I feel this every time I come here,

373
00:45:08,920 --> 00:45:11,700
but your house is very clean.

374
00:45:12,280 --> 00:45:18,160
I wonder what you think about while cleaning around the house.

375
00:45:18,160 --> 00:45:19,770
When I look around your house,

376
00:45:19,770 --> 00:45:24,570
it doesn't seem like you carry an ounce of guilt for killing two people.

377
00:45:31,140 --> 00:45:33,210
Where did you go?

378
00:45:34,760 --> 00:45:36,470
Tell me.

379
00:45:36,470 --> 00:45:41,450
If you can't tell me about it, something inconceivable will happen.

380
00:47:50,100 --> 00:47:52,300
<i>Budu Gang Turf</i>

381
00:49:03,980 --> 00:49:05,630
Run away.

382
00:52:15,110 --> 00:52:17,120
Who are you people?

383
00:52:19,890 --> 00:52:22,990
You should've just managed your district and prepared for retirement.

384
00:52:22,990 --> 00:52:25,640
What more do you have to gain by entering dangerous territory?

385
00:52:25,640 --> 00:52:29,450
I'm an assemblyman.

386
00:52:29,450 --> 00:52:33,760
Are you prepared to face the consequences of your actions?

387
00:52:35,230 --> 00:52:40,540
Assemblyman, don't you know who we are?

388
00:52:46,880 --> 00:52:49,790
Your family is still unharmed, right?

389
00:53:01,840 --> 00:53:04,160
You should be thankful.

390
00:53:55,110 --> 00:53:59,470
Judge Song, did you sleep well?

391
00:53:59,470 --> 00:54:02,180
What is it at this hour?

392
00:54:39,430 --> 00:54:41,000
Yi Hwa...

393
00:54:41,000 --> 00:54:44,340
Yi Hwa! Yi Hwa!

394
00:54:45,640 --> 00:54:48,150
Just what happened to you?

395
00:54:55,260 --> 00:54:58,180
<i>Do not enter - Police Line - Investigation in progress</i>

396
00:55:00,200 --> 00:55:03,390
Most of them are being transferred to Woowon Hospital.

397
00:55:06,930 --> 00:55:09,080
Oh, Prosecutor Kang! Hello.

398
00:55:09,080 --> 00:55:13,370
- Report the state of damages.
- Yes, we're still trying to figure things out.

399
00:55:13,370 --> 00:55:16,940
The injured are currently being transferred to Woowon Hospital.

400
00:55:16,940 --> 00:55:19,060
Are you in your right mind?

401
00:55:19,060 --> 00:55:21,640
Don't you know who did this?

402
00:55:21,640 --> 00:55:25,030
The poor people in this area can't pay the hospital bills.

403
00:55:25,030 --> 00:55:27,730
The police station asked for the hospital's cooperation.

404
00:55:27,730 --> 00:55:31,640
Woowon Hospital replied they'd provide free medical treatment to everyone.

405
00:55:31,640 --> 00:55:35,530
And there's no evidence Woo One is responsible for this.

406
00:55:35,530 --> 00:55:38,860
It's Kim Kang Heon's doing from every angle!

407
00:55:38,860 --> 00:55:41,010
Well...

408
00:55:41,010 --> 00:55:45,450
some people got arrested early this morning.

409
00:55:52,380 --> 00:55:54,080
What's all this about?

410
00:55:54,080 --> 00:55:56,900
They're the leaders of a violent organization

411
00:55:56,900 --> 00:56:00,920
who started the assault on Woowon Pyeonghwa-ro early this morning.

412
00:56:00,920 --> 00:56:04,050
Yes, I'm aware of that. But they're not from Woo One?

413
00:56:04,050 --> 00:56:08,520
They're members of the Seobu Gang, mainly located in the Southwestern areas of Gyeonggi

414
00:56:08,520 --> 00:56:10,800
such as Pyeongchu and Songtaek.

415
00:56:10,800 --> 00:56:13,530
- Why?
- Why, what?

416
00:56:13,530 --> 00:56:18,090
Why did Seobu Gang suddenly attack Budu Gang?

417
00:56:18,090 --> 00:56:22,270
I mean, how should I know why they were fighting amongst—

418
00:56:22,270 --> 00:56:24,730
Today's violence—

419
00:56:24,730 --> 00:56:27,680
Chairman Kim Kang Heon put you up to this, didn't he?

420
00:56:28,460 --> 00:56:33,440
- Who are you to speak down to us in our first meeting?
- Spit it out!

421
00:56:33,440 --> 00:56:36,590
- Prosecutor Kang!
- Kim Kang Heon ordered you to do this!

422
00:56:37,690 --> 00:56:40,320
Chairman Kim Kang Heon of Woo One Group?

423
00:56:40,320 --> 00:56:42,460
Ordered us?

424
00:56:42,460 --> 00:56:44,340
Why would he?

425
00:56:57,880 --> 00:57:00,170
<i>Specialist Jeong Yi Yeob</i>

426
00:57:09,730 --> 00:57:11,390
It doesn't look so good.

427
00:57:11,390 --> 00:57:14,890
He'll have to go to a bigger hospital to be treated properly.

428
00:57:14,890 --> 00:57:18,070
No, treat me here.

429
00:57:18,070 --> 00:57:20,560
No one must find out about this.

430
00:57:21,620 --> 00:57:25,020
- Will you be okay?
- I'm not doing this for you.

431
00:57:25,020 --> 00:57:30,100
I'm doing this because of my family and me.

432
00:57:30,100 --> 00:57:35,140
That guy... He'll do anything...

433
00:57:36,700 --> 00:57:39,630
if he puts his mind to it.

434
00:57:40,750 --> 00:57:44,730
Excuse me. The two of us have something to discuss.

435
00:57:44,730 --> 00:57:47,060
Please give us some privacy.

436
00:57:57,580 --> 00:58:00,390
Why do you think it turned out like this?

437
00:58:02,140 --> 00:58:06,650
Because Jo Mi Yeon handed over information to Kang So Yeong?

438
00:58:06,650 --> 00:58:11,580
Or because Jo Mi Yeon, you,

439
00:58:11,580 --> 00:58:15,870
and I met in secret?

440
00:58:15,870 --> 00:58:18,460
What did we get caught doing?

441
00:58:19,660 --> 00:58:22,700
What do you think happened to Jo Mi Yeon?

442
00:58:42,370 --> 00:58:44,340
The body was found around 7 a.m. this morning

443
00:58:44,340 --> 00:58:47,360
near Route 38 at Haeyang-ro.

444
00:58:47,360 --> 00:58:50,510
We've confirmed the identity. It's Amate Tee Rab.

445
00:58:50,510 --> 00:58:53,520
He was a 21-year-old male from Egypt.

446
00:58:53,520 --> 00:58:55,830
He was identified this quickly?

447
00:58:55,830 --> 00:58:58,880
His passport was inside the pocket of his jacket.

448
00:58:58,880 --> 00:59:02,830
- There was also an expired work visa.
- An illegal immigrant?

449
00:59:02,830 --> 00:59:04,590
But...

450
00:59:05,230 --> 00:59:07,060
there was something odd.

451
00:59:07,060 --> 00:59:11,410
When we got the corpse, its temperature was -1°C.

452
00:59:11,410 --> 00:59:14,410
Usually, in the spring and summer, it begins to decay from inside,

453
00:59:14,410 --> 00:59:18,450
- and it turns above 18°C due to the external temperature.
- That's right.

454
00:59:18,450 --> 00:59:22,610
But I took the temperature because it was so cold and it was -1°C.

455
00:59:23,600 --> 00:59:26,960
I believe someone had stored the corpse in a freezer.

456
00:59:26,960 --> 00:59:28,660
A freezer?

457
00:59:28,660 --> 00:59:32,200
The time of death is currently impossible to estimate.

458
00:59:40,470 --> 00:59:42,040
F***.

459
00:59:42,040 --> 00:59:45,030
- Who is she?
- She said she's Tee Rab's girlfriend.

460
00:59:45,030 --> 00:59:47,850
We asked her to come for identification purposes.

461
00:59:50,670 --> 00:59:52,980
What a f***ing moron.

462
00:59:55,930 --> 00:59:59,200
You said we'd go to Egypt together.

463
00:59:59,200 --> 01:00:02,150
I was waiting for you.

464
01:00:02,150 --> 01:00:05,040
What kind of bullshit is this?

465
01:00:06,330 --> 01:00:09,920
Excuse me. I'm from the police.

466
01:00:10,850 --> 01:00:15,440
When did he say you'll go to Egypt?

467
01:00:15,440 --> 01:00:17,330
Last month.

468
01:00:17,330 --> 01:00:21,910
- Oh, was it for a trip?
- No.

469
01:00:25,410 --> 01:00:29,700
We promised to go to Egypt and get married.

470
01:00:34,500 --> 01:00:37,380
I think he was stored in a freezer unit and

471
01:00:37,380 --> 01:00:40,060
was abandoned at the beach last night,

472
01:00:40,060 --> 01:00:43,840
- so people can see.
- F***...

473
01:00:46,700 --> 01:00:49,800
I heard you two were going to get married.

474
01:00:49,800 --> 01:00:51,430
Yes...

475
01:00:53,320 --> 01:00:57,690
Wouldn't you know who might've done this to your boyfriend?

476
01:01:00,890 --> 01:01:02,890
F-F***...

477
01:01:02,890 --> 01:01:04,760
Those sons of bitches...

478
01:01:04,760 --> 01:01:08,300
What did Tee Rab do wrong?

479
01:01:08,300 --> 01:01:10,680
Tee Rab!

480
01:01:39,900 --> 01:01:44,190
<i>They wanted to speak but could not.</i>

481
01:01:44,190 --> 01:01:47,250
<i>Tears stood in their eyes.</i>

482
01:01:47,250 --> 01:01:50,750
<i>They were both pale and thin.</i>

483
01:01:50,750 --> 01:01:54,170
<i>But those sick pale faces were</i>

484
01:01:54,170 --> 01:01:56,870
<i>bright with the dawn of a new future,</i>

485
01:01:56,870 --> 01:02:02,210
<i>of a full resurrection into a new life.</i>

486
01:02:02,210 --> 01:02:07,130
<i>Epilogue of "Crime and Punishment" by Fyodor Dostoevsky</i>

487
01:02:38,520 --> 01:02:41,870
Na Yeong, please read the breaking news first.

488
01:02:45,770 --> 01:02:50,680
<i>Around 6:30 a.m. this morning, a dead body was found at</i>

489
01:02:50,680 --> 01:02:53,220
<i>1324 Outer Beach Road, Woowon City.</i>

490
01:02:53,220 --> 01:02:56,850
<i>The police arrived at the scene following a report and</i>

491
01:02:56,850 --> 01:03:01,080
<i>found an I.D. and a passport that identified the body.</i>

492
01:03:01,080 --> 01:03:05,500
<i>The dead person was later identified as a 22-year-old foreign laborer.</i>

493
01:03:08,400 --> 01:03:10,730
<i>17 Unread Messages</i>

494
01:03:10,730 --> 01:03:12,640
<i>Park Chang Hyeok</i>

495
01:03:12,640 --> 01:03:14,880
<i>You're a judge!</i>

496
01:03:14,880 --> 01:03:17,830
<i>H-How can a judge kill someone?</i>

497
01:03:17,830 --> 01:03:20,880
<i>Until my last breath, I'll never speak of H-Ho Yeong—</i>

498
01:03:22,970 --> 01:03:27,010
<i>A 22-Year-Old Egyptian Man, Illegal Immigrant, Shot Dead and Corpse Abandoned</i>

499
01:03:40,140 --> 01:03:44,890
<i>Your Honor</i>

500
01:03:44,890 --> 01:03:47,180
♫ <i>At a familiar stop,</i> ♫

501
01:03:47,180 --> 01:03:51,550
♫ <i> you and I realized </i> ♫

